Type of Rule: 3.5-Checking the value of the data in the catalog (Value against catalog)
Rule description: Verifying that the question descriptions are included in the list of 20 different questions asked of the supplier
CATALOG:
"Does your company have an ESG policy or ESG targets in place?" \
"Does your company have a complete ESG strategy?" \
"Is your company a signatory of any relevant regional, national, international or sectoral responsible business or ESG initiatives?" \
"Does your company have an ESG report following an existing standard, where the company discloses their ESG performance indicators?" \ This could be a separate CSR report or a Sustainability section included in the integrated report or website
"Does your ESG strategy have a formal oversight within the company's organization?" \
"Does your company include Sustainable products in their product/commercial offer?" \
"Have you received any administrative penalties or fines related to ESG issues in the past 5 years?" \
"Does your company measure any aspect of its  environmental footprint?" \
"Does your company have specific targets or goals to reduce its  environmental footprint?" \
"Is your company implementing any actions to reduce their environmental footprint?" \
"Does your company have in place an Environmental Management System?" \
"Does your company measure their Greenhouse Gas (GHG) emissions following an international recognised GHGs emissions standard?" \
"Does your company have an emissions reduction target?" \
"Is your company's emission target a Net Zero target?" \
"Does your company source, design, use or manufacture technologies or solutions that will enable the transition to a low-carbon economy?" \ 
"Does your company have a human rights policy?" \
"Does your company have a policy or program to ensure diversity and equal employee opportunities regardless of ethnic origin, gender, age, sexual orientation or political belief?" \
"Does your company have a health and safety management system in place such as ISO 45001?" \
"Does your company have training plans for its employees for the development of their personal and professional skills in the long term?" \
"Does your company have a grievance/complaints handling mechanism related to employee matters (e.g. to report anonymously inappropriate behavior, conflicts, attempted bribery, etc.)?"

The crossover to obtain t_ksan_eom_contract-gf_source_system_sust_type must be done as follows:
 g5m3 = spark.read.parquet(‘/data/master/g5m3/data/t_g5m3_sust_mob_operations')\
 .where(F.col('gf_cutoff_date').isin('date'))
 cdd = spark.read.parquet('/data/master/ksan/data/t_ksan_eom_contract')\
 .where(F.col('gf_cutoff_date').isin(‘date’))
 join_g5m3 _cdd = g5m3 .join(cdd, g5m3 .g_contract_id == cdd.g_contract_id)
Parameters:
RUNNING JOB PARAMS:
     CUTOFF_DATE: Date of the data
     PREVIOUS_CUTOFF_DATE: Previous date to be compared

     extralibs: Link to custom repository
